item.title: Try my server...it used hamachi
item.dc:creator: @s1l4bm4n s1l4bm4n
item.description:
@s1l4bm4n wrote:

Hello, Zanu.
Hamachi does not host servers it mearly makes a virtual connection with other computer. What makes the server is your computer. Java is what mopar uses and Runescape too. To do this you need a server that you want. I have many downloaded and i can use, and through Hamachi people can connect to it. When you download a “server” you should have a file called “run.bat” or “runserver.bat”. When you click on it you should see a thing called “command”. A bunch of text should appear and it will say something like "server started on ip: 127.0.0.1 (not real ip)). When this happens make a network on hamachi and you can advertise it on http://www.moparisthebest.com/serverstatus.php the Server Status page. And soon people will join and come to your server.
S1l4bm4n
